Q: What does FBLA stand for?
A: Future Business Leaders of America
Q: How do I register to be a member of Warren Township High School’s FBLA chapter?

A: Contact your chapter’s sponsors, who can send you an FBLA membership form. After completing this form, you must pay a fee of $20 in order to be officially considered a member and to participate in competitive events.
Q: How do I sign up for a competitive event?
A: Make sure your dues have been paid before the national deadline posted on the national FBLA website, and that you fill out the competitive event sign-up from the monthly general meeting.
Q: What is the purpose of FBLA?
A: FBLA-PBL inspires and prepares students to become community-minded business leaders in a global society through relevant career preparation and leadership experiences. (From National FBLA Website)
Q: How do I get more involved in FBLA?
A: Participating in volunteering, doing school-wide fundraising, competing in competitive events, and going to leadership conferences are all great ways to get more involved in the FBLA community.
